# Frontend Details Pages

This file is the shared rule set for `details` and `detail` pages. Add future rules here; keep them numbered and concise.

## Rule 1. Route and page key consistency

- For a details form, the route/tab key, `PageFrame page_id`, and card `nav_id` prefix must describe the same page.
- Canonical naming uses `details`, not `detail`.
- Prefer indexed ASCII names such as `a024_bi_indicator_details`.
- Use:
  - route/tab key: `a024_bi_indicator_details_<id|new>`
  - `PageFrame page_id`: `a024_bi_indicator_details`
- Treat legacy `*_detail_*` and `*--detail` names as deprecated and migrate touched pages to `details`.

## Rule 2. Card nav id is required

- Every `CardAnimated` in a details page must have a unique `nav_id`.
- If a raw `Card` is used instead of `CardAnimated`, add the same nav-id behavior or migrate to `CardAnimated`.
- When editing an existing details page, add missing `nav_id` to all touched cards.

## Rule 3. Nav id naming

- Format: `<route>_<card_name>`.
- `card_name` must be short, ASCII-only, and reflect the card purpose.
- Good examples:
  - `a024_bi_indicator_details_preview_fields`
  - `a024_bi_indicator_details_preview_render`
  - `a025_bi_dashboard_details_filters_main`

## Rule 4. Info UI for card id

- The same `nav_id` must exist:
  - in component props
  - in the UI Info popup/control
  - in DOM as `id` and/or `data-nav-id`
- The card-level Info UI must allow the user to see and copy the id from the page.

## Rule 5. Allowed layout patterns

- In-scope only: domain/projection pages in `ui/details/`.
- Use only these layout patterns:
  - `TwoColumnOverview`: `detail-grid` → two `detail-grid__col` → stacked `CardAnimated`
  - `SingleCard`: one full-width `CardAnimated` for form/config/meta tabs
  - `DataTab`: one full-width `CardAnimated` for JSON/table/test/linked-record tabs, including loading/error/empty states

## Rule 6. Card content types

- Each in-scope `CardAnimated` must match one of these internal content types:
  - `EditCard`: editable or read-only form controls based on `details-section__title`, `form__group`, `form__label`
  - `ViewCard`: read-only label/value presentation, summary grids, badges, links, or metadata blocks
  - `ActionCard`: interactive cards with controls plus explicit state/result sections
- `ExceptionCard` is allowed only for special-review pages that do not fit the standard types and must not become a reusable default.

## Rule 7. Card content structure

- `EditCard`:
  - start with `details-section__title`
  - use `form__group` for fields
  - use `form__label` for field captions
- `ViewCard`:
  - start with `details-section__title`
  - keep a consistent label/value layout inside the card
  - do not imitate edit forms when no form controls exist
- `ActionCard`:
  - start with `details-section__title`
  - optional `form__hint` is allowed under the title
  - split content into clear controls/state/result sections instead of ad-hoc blocks

## Rule 8. Excluded pages

- Do not force this standard onto pages outside domain/projection `ui/details/`.
- Exclude generic/shared tooling, dashboard/view surfaces, LLM workflow pages, system/admin details, and modal-like pages that are not real details tabs/pages.

## Rule 9. Anti-patterns

- Do not use raw `Card` in standard details pages; migrate to `CardAnimated`.
- Do not use ad-hoc layout wrappers when one of the allowed patterns fits.
- Do not render empty placeholder `<div></div>` blocks instead of omitting a card.
- Do not leave a `CardAnimated` without `nav_id`.
- Do not rely on repeated inline styles for spacing, layout, colors, and typography when a shared class or card type pattern can express the same structure.
- Do not use `CustomCard` as a normal pattern; if the card does not fit `EditCard`, `ViewCard`, or `ActionCard`, treat it as `ExceptionCard` and review it explicitly.

## Rule 10. Editing checklist

- When creating or editing a details page:
  - verify route/page key naming
  - verify the tab fits one of the allowed layout patterns
  - verify each card fits `EditCard`, `ViewCard`, or `ActionCard`
  - verify every card has a unique `nav_id`
  - verify the Info UI is present and usable
  - verify copied ids are searchable in IDE
  - verify the page is not on the exclusions list before refactoring
